dct_description_sm: Prepared under the direction of the Chief of Engineers by the Army Map Service (GE), Corps of Engineers, Department of the Army , [planimetry and contours] by U.S. Geological Survey. Variant title: Indiana 1:25,000. Filing title: Edinburg, Indiana. Standard map series designation: AMS (Series) V851 Sheet 3862 IV SW. AMS 1. Transverse Mercator projection. A.M.S. , V851. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Shows roads, railroads, boundaries, buildings, and natural features. Marginal maps: Index to boundaries -- Index to adjoining sheets. Contour interval 10 feet. "Planimetry by stereophotogrammetric (multiplex) methods by the U. S. Geological Survey, 1946. Countours by plane-table methods by the U. S. Geological Survey 1946-1947. Horizontal and vertical control by USGS and USC&GS. Aerial photography 1944. Public Land Survey lines are based on the Second Principal Meridian and Base Line." "N3915-W8552.5/7.5." "Type C (AMS 1), 1947." "7-48." Printed with vegetation.
Imprint: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, Corps of Engineers, Department of the Army, 1948.
Dimensions: 56 x 45 cm or smaller; Scale: 1:25,000
dct_creator_sm: United States. Army Map Service; Geological Survey (U.S.)
